# Add/Create Button Pattern

For main pages (gastos, presupuestos, plantillas, categorÃ­as, etc.), follow this responsive pattern for the primary creation action:

## Mobile
Use a floating action button (FAB) fixed at the bottom-right:

```tsx
<Button
  size="icon"
  className="fixed bottom-20 right-4 h-14 w-14 rounded-full shadow-lg md:hidden z-40"
>
  <Plus className="h-6 w-6" />
</Button>
```

See [src/app/(app)/gastos/fab.tsx](mdc:src/app/(app)/gastos/fab.tsx) for a real example.

## Desktop
Place a standard button to the right of the page title in a flex row with justify-between:

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-between">
  <div>
    <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Page Title</h1>
    <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Subtitle</p>
  </div>
  <Button className="hidden md:flex">
    <Plus className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
    Nueva plantilla
  </Button>
</div>
```

See [src/app/(app)/plantillas/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/(app)/plantillas/page.tsx) as a reference.

## Combined
- FAB uses `md:hidden` to hide on desktop
- Header button uses `hidden md:flex` to show only on desktop
- Both trigger the same sheet/form/action
